.SH NAME
pdfpcrc \- pdfpc configuration file

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\fBpdfpc\fR(1) first reads its system-wide configuration file, followed by the
user-specific one if it exists.

.SS Keybindings
.PP
The following commands are accepted:
.TP
.B bind <key> <func> [<arg>]
Bind a key to a function, passing a specified argument for functions which require one
.TP
.B unbind <key>
Unbind the given key
.TP
.B unbind_all
Clear all the key bindings
.TP
.B mouse <button> <func>
Bind a mouse button to a function
.TP
.B unmouse <button>
Unbind a mouse button
.TP
.B unmouse_all
Clear all the mouse bindings

.PP
A list of all possible functions can be obtained
via the \-L command line option of \fBpdfpc\fR(1).

.SS Options
.PP
Some permanent changes can be configured via the config file. The syntax is:
.TP
.B option <option_name> <option_value>

.PP
The following option_name's are recognized:

.TP
.B black-on-end
Add an additional black slide at the end of the presentation (bool, Default false)
.TP
.B current-height
Percentage of the height of the presenter screen to be used for the current slide. (int, Default 80)
.TP
.B current-size
Percentage of the presenter screen to be used for the current slide. (int, Default 60)
.TP
.BI disable-caching
see
.B \fBpdfpc\fR(1)
.TP
.BI disable-compression
see
.B \fBpdfpc\fR(1)
.TP
.BI disable-scrolling
Disable scrolling events on the presenter window (bool, Default false)
.TP
.B next-height
Percentage of the height of the presenter screen to be used for the next slide. (int, Default 70)
.TP
.B overview-min-size
Minimum width for the overview miniatures, in pixels. (int, Default 150)
.TP
.B switch-screens
Switch the presentation and the presenter screen. (bool, Default false)
.TP
.B time-of-day
Display the current time instead of the timer
.TP
.B timer-pace-color
Enable color hints of the timer, continuously indicating whether the
presentation is progressing according to the expected pace (bool, Default true).
See the timer operation description in
.B \fBpdfpc\fR(1).
.TP
.B toolbox
Show the toolbox on startup (bool, Default false)
.TP
.B toolbox-direction
Set the toolbox direction (LtoR, RtoL, TtoB, or BtoT for the left-to-right,
right-to-left, top-to-bottom, or botton-to-top, respectively). Default is LtoR.
.TP
.B toolbox-minimized
Set the initial toolbox state minimized (bool, Default false)

.SH EXAMPLES

.PP
Key names can be obtained with the help of the xev utility. Note that
names are case sensitive. Modifiers can be specified in the form
<mod>+<key> where <mod> is one of S (for shift), C (for control) and
A/M (for Alt/Meta). E.g.

.RS
bind S+Next    next10
.RE

.PP
A shorthand for specifying key combinations constituting shift and an
alphabetic character is to simply give the uppercase version of the
alphabetic character. For example, to bind <shift>+r to the 'reset'
function, use

.RS
bind R reset
.RE

.PP
To always activate the black-on-end option, one could add the following to the
config file

.RS
option black-on-end true
.RE

.SH FILES
.PP
.B @SYSCONFDIR@/pdfpcrc
.RS 4
System-wide configuration file
.RE
.PP
.B $XDG_CONFIG_DIR/pdfpc/pdfpcrc
.RS 4
User configuration file (if $XDG_CONFIG_DIR is not set, $HOME/.config will be
used).


.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
\fBpdfpc\fR(1)
